author: kon
msg: Fix bugs that manifested as "free variable" byte-compiler warnings.
* contrib/client-side/psvn/psvn.el
(svn-status-make-dummy-dirs): Don't use the free variable ui-status;
doing so caused all dummy directories to share state with the file
that was found last, yet only one was redisplayed when the status
changed.  Instead, do the same as for files: first try to restore
the UI status from a hash table, and if that fails, construct a
brand new one.
(svn-parse-status-result): Bind dir, which was apparently not
intended to be a free variable.  Propagate the old-ui-information
hash table to svn-status-make-dummy-dirs.
(svn-status-apply-elide-list): Bind elided-list, which was apparently
not intended to be a free variable.
